 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com">Archmage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Nueelien Ravenblood <br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235393" target="top">You dare to inspect me?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nueelien>nueelien</A> at: 11/30/02 10:14:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=buvin>Buvin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/30/02 12:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> Go to &lt;link=<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/recipesearch.html?tradeskill=Brewing>">everquest.allakhazam.com/...l=Brewing></a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->&lt;/link&gt; and work on which ever recipe is above trivial for your skill, and you can cheaply get the ingredients for. Befriend a ranger and they can help out at lower skills (below 100) with foraged stuff. I think short beer, which is pretty cheap and some foraged veggies will get you to 102.  <br>
<br>
Above 102 is where you can start with some of the better stat drinks. In the meantime you get to work on your Alcohol Tolerance. hehehe. <p>Buvin<br>
Half Elvin Ranger<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=458017">Magelao Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=buvin>Buvin</A> at: 11/30/02 12:16:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaspfv>Gasp FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>AKA Brevis</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/2/02 2:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> www.eqtraders.com has all the info you could possibly want about brewing - recipes, where to find supplies, etc.<br>
<br>
To get started in brewing, I'd go to the Plane of Knowledge, find the vendor with fishing grubs and make fetid essence: fishing grub + water.  This takes you all the way to 122.  After that you might want to consider spiced jum jum beer or Ol' Tujim's fierce brew. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ansurfv>AnsurFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/02 10:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> Or grab a Cyclops Skull and make Skull Ale. Skull (always returned to you)+Short Beer+Vinigar+Spices. I took my skull to East Freeport yesaterday and spent about 70pp getting my skill to 136. Now I'll be able to brew my tempers! <br>
Skull Ale trivials at 151<br>
<br>
Ansur<br>
Cleric of Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rubisthenome>Rubis the Nome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/02 10:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> Aye, my suggestion if you really want to power skill brewing is take the skull ale route.  Skull ale can get you 151 skill in 100pp without dealing with casks.  Then get a corking device to do grobb liquidized meats to 216, though this will normally cost you 2500pp or so, you need it for your GM trophy anyhow!  Then Minotaur Hero Brews from 216-248, though they take 9 items to combine.  Or try the dwarven constitutionals but those are heavily dependant on waiting for ground spawns.  Those go to 250 skill however. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=373025">Rubis<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/sigs/rubissig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaspfv>Gasp FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>AKA Brevis</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/02 11:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> I always forget about skull ale.  Remember that the cyclops skull is a giant-sized item, so make sure you have a container in the bank that can hold it.  <br>
<br>
I still would go with fetid essence up to 122 before the skull ale though - 2 ingredients vs 4 means less clicks and faster attempts.<br>
<br>
Lastly, spiced Jum Jum beer is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>very</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> cost efficient if you're worried about expense.  At least it was a couple of months ago - Verant may have corrected some prices. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rubisthenome>Rubis the Nome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/02 3:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> Aye, fetid essence is harder to do if you don't have access to cabilsi for the fishing grubs though.  Also Jumjum is good and cost efficient assuming you brought alot of bag space, yield 10. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=373025">Rubis<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/sigs/rubissig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ansurfv>AnsurFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/02 4:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> Easy way to store the skull is to put a Traders Satchel in the bank (my bank has 7 trader's satchels at a time). 10 slots each and can hold giant items. Or the Deluxe Toolbox is a lighter weight alternative. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maeroth>Maeroth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/10/02 4:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> If you have PoP, you can find a vendor selling fishing grubs in the Plane of Tranquility. I don't know the vendor's name, but if you are headed to the PoN zoneline, go up the stairs to the right as you leave the beach. The first vendor in that building sells em for a few pennies.<br>
<br>
FYI, i went to 122 in brewing with 20 stacks of grubs and 20 stacks of water flasks.  Click-click-combine four hundred times = 122 in Brewing! <br>
<br>
Very easy,,, very cheap.  I think i did this for less than 20pp <p><p align="center"><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=210000>Maeroth Willbender</a><br></b>Erudite Illusionist of 53 Winters <BR> High Counselor of <a href=http://hoc.eq.tripod.com>The House of Carnage</a><br>follower of Quellious the peaceful, and enemy of all who stand against her <BR><select name=tradeskills><option>Grand Master Jeweler 250 +5%<option>Master Baiter 165<option>Master Baker 143<option>Master Potter 132<option>Master Brewer 120<option>Pathetic Tailor 21</select></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sywyn@firionavie>Sywyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 4:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> Do they have to be bought fishing grubs or can they be foraged?  Guess I'll find out soon enough.<br>
<br>
Route I've taken so far is trying to make Vodka, but I have a druid friend that forages like crazy, so the veggies come fast and furious. Only pay for the short beer, water and bottles.<br>
<br>
Silly me sold my only cyclops skull in the bazaar before Ansur told me what it was for, and I have yet to loot another one.<br>
<br>
Sywyn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ansurfv>AnsurFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 4:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> Well, I could loan you mine. I trust you enough to give it back. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trump13>Trump13</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/02 12:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=496.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: brewing - need to learn</span><hr size=1> Vendor in PoK sells grubs... little gnome.<br>
